frameDefinitions: The words in this frame describe an Experiencer's emotions with respect to some Content.
An Experiencer feels an emotion as evoked as an Other.
An Agent performs a Response action in consequence of a Trigger event.
An Experiencer desires that an Event occur.
A Self_mover leaves an initial Source location.
frameExamples: My <t>enjoyment</t> of the movie was considerably impaired by the seven-foot guy sitting in front of me.
One might <t>pity</t> the frail old man in East Berlin.
I <t>respond</t> to earthquakes by hiding under my desk.
I only <t>wanted</t> one piece of candy.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Experiencer</fen> experiences the emotion or other internal state.

<fen>Content</fen> is what the <fen>Experiencer</fen>'s feelings or experiences are directed towards or based upon.  The <fen>Content</fen> differs from a stimulus because the <fen>Content</fen> is not construed as being direcly responsible for causing the emotion.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is the area about which the <fen>Experiencer</fen> has the particular experience.
The <fen>Event</fen> is the occasion or happening that <fen>Experiencer</fen>s in a certain emotional state participate in.
The time at which the <fen>Experiencer</fen> is in the specified emotional state.
The <fen>Experiencer</fen> is the person or sentient entity that experiences or feels the emotions.
The <fen>Other</fen> is the person that evokes the emotional response in the <fen>Experiencer</fen>.
The  <fen>Situation</fen> is the circumstances or topic about which the <fen>Experiencer</fen> feels an emotion.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Experiencer</fen> feels for the <fen>Other</fen>.
A non-agentive entity that is impinged upon by a <fen>Trigger</fen> event to which they respond.
An event that impinges upon the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Responding_entity</fen> and produces a <fen>Response</fen> from it.
The intentional <fen>Agent</fen> that is impinged upon by a <fen>Trigger</fen> event to which they respond.
The point in time when the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Responding_entity</fen> manifests its <fen>Response</fen> to the <fen>Trigger</fen> .
The location in which the <fen>Response</fen> action takes place.
The <fen>Experiencer</fen> is the person (or sentient being) who wishes for the <fen>Event</fen> to occur.
The change that the <fen>Experiencer</fen> would like to see.
This is the entity that the <fen>Experiencer</fen> wishes to be affected by some <fen>Event</fen>.
The <fen>Location_of_event</fen> is the place involved in the desired <fen>Event</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Experiencer</fen> desires something.
Where the event takes place.  Note that this role is of extremely rare occurrence in this frame.
This is the entity which moves under its own power.

Any expression which implies a definite starting-point of motion expresses the frame element <fen>Source</fen>. In prepositional phrases, the prepositional object expresses the starting point of motion. In particles, the starting point of motion is understood from context.
The time at which the motion takes place.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the motion (which is specified by a <fen>Source</fen>, <fen>Path</fen> or <fen>Goal</fen>) is located.
listRoleExamples: Mr. Whiskers was upset <fex>about his cat treats</fex>.
It felt pretty awkward to partake in such a nervous <fex>ceremony</fex>.
<fex>Last year</fex>, Bob was still interested in the young Republicans.
How has the modern welfare state responded <fex>to the needs of working class women</fex>, and why?
Once again <fex>the Government</fex> is responding to a crisis with measures that will only harm patients
Israel responded <fex>yesterday</fex> to the killing of 22 people by Palestinian suicide bombers with a helicopter attack

The auto industry has responded <fex>in the U.S., but particularly in Asian and European markets</fex> by manufacturing an entry-level segment of cars that is more appealing, better looking, and safer than in the past.
I want that box <fex>on top of the other one</fex>.
Oh, so <fex>now</fex> you want to go to the zoo!
<fex>In the car</fex> I had desired nothing more than to get here, but now that I'm here...
